// Man page for median
manMedian="MEDIAN(1)                        X Shell Manual                        MEDIAN(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    median - Find median value in list
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>median NUMBER</b> [NUMBER...]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Calculate the median (middle value) of a list of numbers.
    For odd-length lists, returns the middle number. For even-length
    lists, typically returns the average of the two middle numbers.
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <b>median 1 2 3 4 5</b>
    Find median of 5 numbers (result: 3)

    <b>median 10 20 30</b>
    Find median of 3 numbers (result: 20)

    <b>median 5 15 25 35</b>
    Find median of 4 numbers
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>average</b>, <b>percent</b>"